div.p:
Wilt thou receiue I ſay thy full fraught at once, and the totall ſumme of all thine infelicities, thou haſt no intereſt in God, no ſociety with the Saints, no fellowſhip with the beleeuers, no parte or portion in any the good creatures of God: ful of terror and aſtoniſhment, is that ſaying of Saint Iohn; 
                  Reu. 21. 8 the fearefull, and vnbeleeuing, and abhominable, and murtherers, and ſorcerers, and all lyers, ſhall haue their portion in

 the lake that burnes with fire, and brimſtone.
